    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-08-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="706"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d706">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">O’Brien</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-08-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 25, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. O’Brien reports that an official note from the minister for foreign affairs
                    which he has just received incloses the text of the treaty with Korea, already
                    given him informally, and says the treaty comes in force August 29, the date of
                    its promulgation. Mr. O’Brien adds that the note states that— <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>In view of the treaty relations actually subsisting between the United
                            States and, Korea I have the honor to convey the above to your
                            excellency’s knowledge before the promulgation and coming into force of
                            the said treaty.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
